---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Tacky Turquoise collects, uses, and protects your information."
>
  <section class="policy">
    <div class="policy__inner">
      <div class="policy__crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> &nbsp;/&nbsp; Privacy Policy</div>

      <h1>Privacy <em>Policy.</em></h1>
      <p class="policy__updated">Last updated: 4/25/2026</p>

      <p class="policy__lede">
        This Privacy Policy describes how Tacky Turquoise (Apex Quality Analytics LLC)
        collects, uses, and protects information when you visit tackyturquoise.com or
        place an order.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Collect</h2>
      <p><strong>Information you give us:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Name, email, phone number, and shipping address (when you place an order)</li>
        <li>Payment information (handled directly by Stripe — we never see or store full card numbers)</li>
        <li>Order notes you choose to include</li>
        <li>Any messages you send us</li>
      </ul>

      <p><strong>Information collected automatically:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Browser type, device type, IP address, pages visited, and time spent on the Site</li>
        <li>Cart contents stored in your browser's local storage</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use It</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To process and fulfill your orders</li>
        <li>To send order confirmations, shipping notifications, and respond to questions</li>
        <li>To calculate accurate shipping rates and sales tax</li>
        <li>To detect fraud and protect the Site from abuse</li>
        <li>To improve the Site based on aggregate usage patterns</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>We do not sell your personal information. Ever.</strong></p>

      <h2>Who We Share It With</h2>
      <p>We share information only with service providers who help us operate the Site:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — payment processing (PCI-compliant; processes card information directly without us seeing it)</li>
        <li><strong>Shippo</strong> — shipping rate calculation and label generation</li>
        <li><strong>Resend</strong> — transactional emails (order confirmations and shipping notifications)</li>
        <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — secure database hosting for orders and product information</li>
        <li><strong>Netlify</strong> — site hosting and content delivery</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Each of these providers has their own privacy policies and security practices.
        We choose providers known for strong data protection.
      </p>
      <p>
        We may also disclose information if required by law, subpoena, or court order,
        or to protect our legal rights.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and Tracking</h2>
      <p>We use minimal browser storage (cookies and localStorage) to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Remember your cart between visits</li>
        <li>Keep admin users logged in to internal accounts if applicable</li>
        <li>Measure aggregate site usage</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can disable cookies in your browser, but parts of the Site may not function correctly.</p>

      <h2>Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use industry-standard security measures to protect your information, including
        HTTPS encryption for all transmissions, secure database hosting, and limited
        internal access. However, no method of internet transmission is 100% secure, and
        we cannot guarantee absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal information we have about you</li>
        <li><strong>Correct</strong> inaccurate information</li>
        <li><strong>Delete</strong> your information (subject to legal record-keeping requirements for completed orders)</li>
        <li><strong>Opt out</strong> of any non-essential communications</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise these rights, email us at
        <a href="mailto:orders@tackyturquoise.com">orders@tackyturquoise.com</a>.
        We'll respond within 30 days.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you're a California or Colorado resident, you have additional rights under
        the CCPA and Colorado Privacy Act, including the right to opt out of any sale of
        personal information (which we don't do).
      </p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect
        information from children. If we learn we have collected information from a child
        under 13, we will delete it promptly.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep order information for as long as required by tax and accounting laws
        (typically 7 years in the US). Account-related information is kept until you
        request deletion or the account becomes inactive.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy at any time. The "Last updated" date reflects
        the most recent revision. Material changes will be communicated via email if
        appropriate.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy-related questions or to exercise your rights, email
        <a href="mailto:orders@tackyturquoise.com">orders@tackyturquoise.com</a>.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p class="policy__signoff">
        <strong>Apex Quality Analytics LLC</strong>
        DBA Tacky Turquoise<br />
        Olathe, Colorado
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Footer />
</Base>
